1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
What if I told you carbon is a shape-shifter?

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:08,800
Carbon moves between the air, oceans, rocks, and life, creating a delicate balance.

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:13,600
But what happens when we overload one of these reservoirs with CO2?

4
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:20,000
Human fossil fuel emissions are pushing carbon into the atmosphere faster than it can cycle back.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,600
This overload disrupts ecosystems, weather patterns, and our future.

6
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:28,400
Stay curious and learn how you can help balance the carbon cycle.

7
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:29,600
Follow for more!
